                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/58</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Berne</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-05T10:00:00+01:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">November 5, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>The director of the Swiss People’s Bank claims that all his recent telegrams to
                    New York banks relating to money transfers have not <pb facs="0828" n="514"
                        xml:id="pg_514"/> reached their destination. He stated also that telegrams
                    from Swiss banks to the United States ordering grain to be furnished Swiss
                    Government had been stopped somewhere and never reached the United States. It is
                    believed that England and France are censoring such telegrams. Swiss bankers
                    protest as this interferes materially with the business between Switzerland and
                    America.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
